    <h1>FPGA SiP and Evolvable Hardware</h1>
    <p style="color: #64748b; font-size: 0.9rem;">Category: Space / Defense</p>

    <div class="audio-section">
        <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-weight: bold;">Listen to Audio:</p>
        <audio controls src="../../3d.mp3" style="width: 100%;"></audio>
    </div>

    <div class="script-box">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">English Script</h3>
        <p><b>A (Chronix):</b> For the Mars mission, we’re proposing the FPGA SiP (System-in-Package) integrated with 3D stacking technology.</p>
        <p><b>B:</b> Why not use a standard radiation-hardened ASIC? It’s usually more power-efficient.</p>
        <p><b>A:</b> True, but in deep space, physical maintenance is impossible. With FPGA, we can remotely reconfigure the hardware logic to adapt to unexpected sensor failures or new mission requirements.</p>
        <p><b>B:</b> I see. So the 3D integration allows you to pack high-density processing into a tiny, radiation-shielded footprint?</p>
        <p><b>A:</b> Exactly. It’s about creating "evolvable hardware" that can survive and optimize itself in the most extreme environments.</p>
    </div>

    <button class="btn-toggle" onclick="toggleJp()">日本語訳を表示/非表示</button>

    <div class="jp-box" id="jpBox">
        <h3>日本語訳</h3>
        <p><b>A:</b> 火星探査ミッションに向けて、3D積層技術を統合したFPGA SiP（システム・イン・パッケージ）を提案しています。</p>
        <p><b>B:</b> 標準的な放射線耐性ASICを使わないのはなぜですか？</p>
        <p><b>A:</b> 深宇宙では物理的なメンテナンスが不可能です。FPGAであれば、ロジックを遠隔で再構成でき、予期せぬ故障にも対応できます。</p>
        
        <div class="study-grid">
